                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12681123" author="evangilbert" created="Thu, 12 Mar 2009 00:58:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Wondering how people would feel about returning application/javascript instead of application/json?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve rarely seen application/json used, probably because debugging is very difficult with application/json as most browsers treat the content as a binary file and try to download it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Application/javascript will also work with JSONP when we enable it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12681124" author="chabotc" created="Thu, 12 Mar 2009 01:03:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;there&apos;s a lot of live sites who use application/json, patching this in shindig trunk isn&apos;t going to change that reality and having different (non-spec-defined) content-types set would only lead to confusion in my opinion&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12716764" author="plindner" created="Fri, 5 Jun 2009 21:52:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;checked into trunk&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
